Sure, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "pokupio" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations in parentheses:

1. Juče sam *pokupio* sve igračke koje su bile razbacane po sobi. (Yesterday I *picked up* all the toys that were scattered around the room.)

2. On je sinoć *pokupio* sve nagrade na dodeli filmskih nagrada. (He *swept up* all the awards at the film awards ceremony last night.)

3. Molim te, *pokupi* knjige sa stola i stavi ih u biblioteku. (Please *collect* the books from the table and put them in the library.)

4. Kada je video da pada kiša, brzo je *pokupio* veš sa žice. (When he saw that it was raining, he quickly *gathered up* the laundry from the clothesline.)

5. Moja baka je nekada *pokupila* grožđe u vinogradu, ali sada više ne može. (My grandmother used to *pick* grapes in the vineyard, but now she can't anymore.)

6. Naš tim je sinoć teško *pokupio* poraz od protivničke ekipe. (Our team suffered a heavy *defeat* at the hands of the opposing team last night.)

7. Nije mi jasno kako si mogao da *pokupiš* sve te povrede u samo jednoj utakmici. (I don't understand how you managed to *pick up* all those injuries in just one game.)

8. Kada je videla da je neko *pokupio* novčanice sa stola, odmah je pozvala policiju. (When she saw that someone had *taken* the banknotes from the table, she immediately called the police.)

9. Naše društvo je *pokupilo* dosta novca za humanitarne akcije tokom godine. (Our group *collected* a lot of money for charitable causes throughout the year.)

Note: The asterisk (*) is not used in Serbian to indicate the word being highlighted, but I have included it for clarity.